    <h4>Learning in the Rodent Motor Cortex.</h4>
    <h5>Peters AJ, Liu H, Komiyama T, Annual </h5>
    <p>
        Activity in motor cortex corticospinal neurons are flexibly
        related to movement across days but becomes more distinguishable
        for learned movements. This suggests that the output of the 
        cortex to the spinal cord is constantly shifting even to produce
        similar movements, but learning drives activity patterns to become
        more unique for dissimilar movements.        
    </p>
</div>

