    <h4>Emergence of reproducible spatiotemporal activity during motor learning.</h4>
    <h5>Peters AJ, Chen S, Komiyama T, Nature 2014</h5>
    <p>
        Activity in L2/3 of the motor cortex is flexibly related to 
        movement, becoming more consistent for learned movements. This
        suggests that networks of neurons one step before cortical output 
        become specialized for learned movements.
    </p>
</div>

